classes.title: CLASS MUS LIVE
classes.description: Students meet for a one-hour pre-concert lecture given by   Music Department faculty, and then attend world-class symphony   concerts sponsored by Santa Barbara's Community Arts Music   Association.

classes.title: INTRO MUSIC STUDIES
classes.description: Introduces students to ways of studying music as a cultural   practice situated in society. Methods are drawn from   musicology, ethnomusicology, history, anthropology, and   sociology. Students will be taught to think critically about   music as a universal human expression.

classes.title: MUSICIANSHIP
classes.description: A practical course in sight singing, aural analysis, and   rhythmic studies.

classes.title: MUSICIANSHIP
classes.description: A practical course in sight singing, aural analysis, and   rhythmic studies.

classes.title: THEORY: ANALYSIS II
classes.description: Secondary dominants, diatonic modulation, chromatic chords,   sequences.

classes.title: CLASS COMPOSITION
classes.description: Assignments in basics of music writing.

classes.title: HISTORY OF MUSIC C
classes.description: A survey of Western music and its social contexts from 1848 to 1945. Topics include music and nationalism, late romanticism and the limits of tonality , modernism, the impact of popular music on art music, and neoclassicism.

classes.title: FUNDAMENTALS OF MUS
classes.description: The study of notes, scales, triads, inversions, rhythm, harmony, and musical terminology. Laboratory activities include keyboard orientation, sight singing, and ear training.

classes.title: MUSIC APPRECIATION
classes.description: A selective survey of music of western civilization; evolution of forms, styles, media. Designed to enable the student to listen with understanding.

classes.title: LISTENING TO JAZZ
classes.description: Aims to unravel the mystery of Jazz?s allure, importance,  and performance  process, in a manner mostly divorced from  technical musical terminology or  music theory, through targeted readings, listening assignments, written pr ojects, in-class visits, and concert attendance.

classes.title: WORLD MUSIC
classes.description: An introductory course surveying the unity and diversity of folk, traditional, and classical music of the non-western world. Emphasis given to dance, theatre, musical instruments, and the role of music in society.

classes.title: ELMNTRY VOICE I
classes.description: Elementary voice lessons at beginning level. Placement in Music A, B, or C will be determined by the instructor after an audition.

classes.title: ELMNTRY VOICE II
classes.description: Elementary voice lessons designed for those with a small amount of vocal experience.

classes.title: ELMNTRY VOICE III
classes.description: Elementary voice lessons designed for those who have significant vocal training and experience.

classes.title: DASTGAH
classes.description: An examination of the system of melodic modes (dastgah) that governs practice in the   Persian/Iranian music. Emphasis given to theoretical issues (scales, intervals, and melodic   progressions) and analysis of standard repertoire. Students will receive introductory   lessons on Persian instruments(the setar and tar).

classes.title: MAQAM
classes.description: Applied instruction in non-Western instruments: the Arabic   maqam, the system of melodic modes used in traditional   Arabic music.

classes.title: NAY
classes.description: Applied instruction in non-Western instruments: the Middle-  Eastern nay (end-blown flute).

classes.title: OUD
classes.description: Applied instruction in the Middle Eastern oud (lute).

classes.title: CLASS PIANO
classes.description: Black key minor scales (natural/harmonic) and chords.   Preparing for the proficiency exam: review of all scales and   chords, more advanced harmonization, transposition. Learning a   solo piece from the list of the appropriate repertoire.

classes.title: CLASS PIANO
classes.description: Optional continuation of Music 31. Equivalent in level to Music 32. Elementary individual class piano instruction in class or individual context. Includes scales, sight reading, transposition, harmonization at the keyboard, with emphasis on piano literature.

classes.title: SECONDARY PIANO
classes.description: Optional continuation of Music 31. Elementary individual class piano instruction. Includes scales, sight reading, transposition, harmonization at the keyboard, with emphasis on piano literature.

classes.description: Third quarter of a 3-quarter series course will concentrate on   real-time computer music composition with micro-computers and   digital synthesis/processing equipment.

classes.title: MUSIC & POP CULTURE
classes.description: A survey of the relationships between music and popular   culture in America. Music to be discussed includes blues,   jazz, and rock, as well as classical music. Emphasis is on   cultural, rather than technical aspects of music.

classes.title: MIDDLE EAST MUSIC
classes.description: Arab, Turkish, and Persian music traditions from historical, cultural, and musicological perspectives. Emphasis given to the position of music in Islam, present-day performers, and modal and rhythmic structures.

classes.title: POLISH FOLK MUSIC
classes.description: The Tatras are the home of a distinct folk culture, including music based on polyphonic singing ad violin ensembles. Course investigates the present-day music from this region and its history, and examines the influence of tourism and ethnography on the music-culture.
